<h2 dir="ltr">SADAD Information Security Policy</h2>
<h3 dir="ltr">Introduction</h3>
<p dir="ltr">SADAD mission is “To be the leader provider of state of
	the art electronic billing and payment solutions in Saudi Arabia and
	the region”</p>
<p dir="ltr">It is the policy of the company to secure SADAD in a
	manner which meets or exceeds accepted best practice, ensure business
	continuity, minimize business damage and maximize return on investment.</p>
<h3 dir="ltr">Policy Scope</h3>
<p dir="ltr">This policy applies to all SADAD’s information assets
	and users of those assets including employees, temporary staff,
	contractors, service providers, business partners and other third
	parties. Such assets include data that is stored on computers,
	transmitted across networks, printed out or written on paper, sent by
	fax, stored on backup tapes, CD’s and diskettes or spoken in
	conversation.</p>
<h3 dir="ltr">Policy Objective</h3>
<p dir="ltr">To ensure that SADAD provides and implements adequate
	information security controls that will protect its information assets,
	in all forms from unauthorised use, duplication, modification,
	disclosure and destruction.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The aim of information security at SADAD is to ensure:</p>
<ul dir="ltr">
	<li>Confidentiality – information is accessible only to those
		authorised for access;</li>
	<li>Integrity – information is accurate and complete including
		processing methods;</li>
	<li>Availability – authorised users can have access to information
		when required.</li>
</ul>
<p dir="ltr">It is our policy to ensure that:</p>
<ul dir="ltr">
	<li>All client data is appropriately protected and is not divulged
		to any third party without authorisation;</li>
	<li>The premises are protected by suitable physical security and
		environmental controls, and where appropriate, access is restricted to
		authorised staff;</li>
	<li>Confidentiality and integrity of all information is
		maintained; information is accessible to all staff according to
		business need and is protected against unauthorised access;</li>
	<li>Access to organisational data and personal data is
		appropriately controlled;</li>
	<li>Contractual, regulatory and legislative requirements are met;</li>
	<li>A business continuity plan is devised, tested and maintained;</li>
	<li>All in house systems development is appropriately controlled
		and tested before live implementation;</li>
	<li>All staff are provided with training in information security
		awareness and individual responsibilities defined;</li>
	<li>All staff are aware of their responsibility to adhere to the
		policy and ensure that all breaches of information security, actual or
		suspected are reported to and investigated by the Information Security
		Board</li>
</ul>
<p dir="ltr">This policy provides a clear statement of our
	commitment to protect all information assets from threats internal and
	external, intentional or accidental. This policy is issued and
	maintained by the Quality Assurance and Information Security Manager,
	who also provides advice and guidance on its implementation and ensures
	compliance. All staff and consultants within the company are directly
	responsible for implementing and complying with this policy.</p>
<h3 dir="ltr">Breaches</h3>
<p dir="ltr">All breaches actual or suspected, of this policy must
	be reported to one’s immediate manager, the Service Control System and
	the Quality Assurance and Information Security Manager who will ensure
	they are investigated.</p>
<p dir="ltr">All breaches or violation of this policy may result in
	severe penalties, including, but not limited to, disciplinary process
	up to termination of employment and/or legal action/prosecution.</p>
<h3 dir="ltr">Policy Ownership and Maintenance</h3>
<p dir="ltr">This policy is owned and maintained by the Quality
	Assurance and Information Security Manager; it is reviewed whenever
	there is a change to the legal and regulatory environment, information
	security best practice and or SADAD business processes. When no such
	changes occur the document will be reviewed at least annually to ensure
	that it continues to reflect information security best practices.</p>
<p dir="ltr">The information security management system (ISMS)
	provides the framework for the implementation of this policy within the
	company and is supported by a comprehensive set of procedures. This
	system is regularly reviewed via a risk management and management
	review process to ensure that all identified risks are covered.</p>
<p dir="ltr">This policy has been approved by the management of
	SADAD.</p>